If you are learning jQuery, then doing AJAX with jQuery is extremely easy.<p>First, you have to learn how code a server side application that send JSON or XML encoded data.<p>Then you can load it with jquery using .ajax like so:<p><pre><code>    $.ajax({url: 'yoururl.com/script',

        data: 'field1': 'myval',

        success: function(data)

        {

            //call to server worked, json/xml has been auto

            //inflated into the data object
        },

        error: function()

        {

            //the call failed, maybe a 404 or 500 error.

        });

</code></pre>
That's it!  You'll want to then manipulate your DOM accordingly, such as disabling any 'buttons' setting progress status, etc.
